.TH DUPLICATES\-DETECTOR "1" "2026\-04\-09" "duplicates\-detector 3.0.5.dev4+g6a1dea7ea.d20260408" "Duplicates Detector Manual"
.SH NAME
duplicates\-detector \- detect duplicate video, image, and audio files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B duplicates\-detector
[-h] [--version] [--print-completion SHELL] {scan} ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Detect duplicate/similar video or image files by comparing metadata and filenames.

.SH
POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fBduplicates\-detector\fR \fI\,scan\/\fR
Scan directories for duplicates (default)

.SH COMMAND \fI\,'duplicates\-detector scan'\/\fR
usage: duplicates\-detector scan [\-h] [\-\-no\-recursive] [\-\-threshold N]
                                [\-\-workers N] [\-\-extensions EXT,EXT]
                                [\-\-exclude PATTERN] [\-\-reference DIR]
                                [\-\-min\-size SIZE] [\-\-max\-size SIZE]
                                [\-\-min\-duration SECS] [\-\-max\-duration SECS]
                                [\-\-min\-resolution WxH] [\-\-max\-resolution WxH]
                                [\-\-min\-bitrate RATE] [\-\-max\-bitrate RATE]
                                [\-\-codec CODEC,...] [\-v] [\-q] [\-\-no\-color]
                                [\-\-machine\-progress] [\-\-content]
                                [\-\-content\-method METHOD]
                                [\-\-rotation\-invariant] [\-\-audio]
                                [\-\-no\-audio\-cache] [\-\-no\-content\-cache]
                                [\-\-no\-metadata\-cache] [\-\-no\-pre\-hash]
                                [\-\-sidecar\-extensions EXTS] [\-\-no\-sidecars]
                                [\-\-cache\-dir DIR] [\-\-min\-score N]
                                [\-\-weights SPEC] [\-\-ignore\-file PATH]
                                [\-\-mode MODE] [\-\-no\-config] [\-\-profile NAME]
                                [\-i] [\-\-dry\-run] [\-\-keep STRATEGY]
                                [\-\-action ACTION] [\-\-move\-to\-dir DIR]
                                [\-\-group] [\-\-sort FIELD] [\-\-limit N]
                                [\-\-format FORMAT] [\-\-json\-envelope]
                                [\-\-embed\-thumbnails] [\-\-thumbnail\-size WxH]
                                [\-\-output FILE] [\-\-clear\-ignored] [\-\-log FILE]
                                [\-\-generate\-undo LOG_FILE]
                                [\-\-resume SESSION_ID] [\-\-list\-sessions]
                                [\-\-delete\-session SESSION_ID]
                                [\-\-clear\-sessions] [\-\-pause\-file PATH]
                                [\-\-cache\-stats] [\-\-save\-config]
                                [\-\-show\-config] [\-\-save\-profile NAME]
                                [\-\-replay FILE]
                                [directories ...]

.TP
\fBdirectories\fR
Directories to scan (default: current directory)

.SH OPTIONS \fI\,'duplicates\-detector scan'\/\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-recursive\fR
Only scan the top\-level directory, not subdirectories

.TP
\fB\-\-threshold\fR \fI\,N\/\fR
Minimum similarity score (0\-100) to report (default: 50)

.TP
\fB\-\-workers\fR \fI\,N\/\fR
Number of parallel workers (default: auto\-detect based on CPU cores)

.TP
\fB\-\-extensions\fR \fI\,EXT,EXT\/\fR
Comma\-separated video extensions to match (e.g., mp4,mkv,avi)

.TP
\fB\-\-exclude\fR \fI\,PATTERN\/\fR
Glob pattern to exclude paths (repeatable, e.g., \-\-exclude '**/thumbnails/**')

.TP
\fB\-\-reference\fR \fI\,DIR\/\fR
Reference directory — files participate in comparison but are never deleted
(repeatable)

.TP
\fB\-\-min\-size\fR \fI\,SIZE\/\fR
Minimum file size to include (e.g., 10MB, 1.5GB, 500KB)

.TP
\fB\-\-max\-size\fR \fI\,SIZE\/\fR
Maximum file size to include (e.g., 10MB, 1.5GB, 500KB)

.TP
\fB\-\-min\-duration\fR \fI\,SECS\/\fR
Minimum duration in seconds to include

.TP
\fB\-\-max\-duration\fR \fI\,SECS\/\fR
Maximum duration in seconds to include

.TP
\fB\-\-min\-resolution\fR \fI\,WxH\/\fR
Minimum resolution to include (e.g., 1280x720, 1920x1080)

.TP
\fB\-\-max\-resolution\fR \fI\,WxH\/\fR
Maximum resolution to include (e.g., 1920x1080, 3840x2160)

.TP
\fB\-\-min\-bitrate\fR \fI\,RATE\/\fR
Minimum container bitrate to include (e.g., 1000000, 5Mbps, 500kbps)

.TP
\fB\-\-max\-bitrate\fR \fI\,RATE\/\fR
Maximum container bitrate to include (e.g., 20Mbps, 50000kbps)

.TP
\fB\-\-codec\fR \fI\,CODEC,...\/\fR
Restrict to specific video codecs (comma\-separated, e.g., h264,hevc,av1)

.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Show detailed progress information and full file paths

.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-quiet\fR
Suppress progress bars and summary output

.TP
\fB\-\-no\-color\fR
Disable colored output

.TP
\fB\-\-machine\-progress\fR
Emit JSON\-lines progress events to stderr (for GUI frontends)

.TP
\fB\-\-content\fR
Enable content\-based perceptual hashing for more accurate detection (slower)

.TP
\fB\-\-content\-method\fR \fI\,METHOD\/\fR
Content method: phash (PDQ perceptual hash, default for video/image), ssim
(structural similarity), clip (CLIP ViT\-B/32 embeddings), simhash (SimHash
text fingerprint, default for document), tfidf (TF\-IDF cosine similarity,
document only)

.TP
\fB\-\-rotation\-invariant\fR
Compute content hashes for all rotations and flips (4\-8x slower, catches
rotated/flipped duplicates). Only affects image mode.

.TP
\fB\-\-audio\fR
Enable Chromaprint audio fingerprinting for more accurate video duplicate
detection (requires fpcalc)

.TP
\fB\-\-no\-audio\-cache\fR
Disable disk cache for audio fingerprints (re\-extract every run)

.TP
\fB\-\-no\-content\-cache\fR
Disable disk cache for content hashes (re\-extract every run)

.TP
\fB\-\-no\-metadata\-cache\fR
Disable disk cache for metadata (re\-run ffprobe on every file)

.TP
\fB\-\-no\-pre\-hash\fR
Disable pre\-hash computation (MD5 of first 4KB) used for byte\-identical
detection

.TP
\fB\-\-sidecar\-extensions\fR \fI\,EXTS\/\fR
Comma\-separated sidecar extensions to detect (default: .xmp,.aae,.thm,.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-no\-sidecars\fR
Disable sidecar file detection and co\-deletion

.TP
\fB\-\-cache\-dir\fR \fI\,DIR\/\fR
Directory for metadata and content hash caches (default:
XDG_CACHE_HOME/duplicates\-detector)

.TP
\fB\-\-min\-score\fR \fI\,N\/\fR
Minimum similarity score (0\-100) to include in results

.TP
\fB\-\-weights\fR \fI\,SPEC\/\fR
Custom comparator weights (e.g.,
'filename=50,duration=30,resolution=10,filesize=10')

.TP
\fB\-\-ignore\-file\fR \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Path to the ignored\-pairs JSON file (default: $XDG_DATA_HOME/duplicates\-
detector/ignored\-pairs.json)

.TP
\fB\-\-mode\fR \fI\,MODE\/\fR
Detection mode: video (default), image, audio, auto (mixed media), or document

.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-interactive\fR
Interactively review each pair and choose files to delete

.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Preview interactive deletions without removing files

.TP
\fB\-\-keep\fR \fI\,STRATEGY\/\fR
Auto\-select which file to keep: newest, oldest, biggest, smallest, longest,
highest\-res, edited

.TP
\fB\-\-action\fR \fI\,ACTION\/\fR
Deletion method: delete (default), trash, move\-to, hardlink, symlink, or
reflink

.TP
\fB\-\-move\-to\-dir\fR \fI\,DIR\/\fR
Staging directory for \-\-action move\-to

.TP
\fB\-\-group\fR
Group transitive duplicates into clusters instead of showing pairs

.TP
\fB\-\-sort\fR \fI\,FIELD\/\fR
Sort results by: score (default), size, path, or mtime

.TP
\fB\-\-limit\fR \fI\,N\/\fR
Maximum number of pairs (or groups) to display

.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI\,FORMAT\/\fR
Output format: table (default), json, csv, shell, html, or markdown

.TP
\fB\-\-json\-envelope\fR
Wrap JSON output in envelope with version, args, and stats

.TP
\fB\-\-embed\-thumbnails\fR
Embed base64 thumbnails in JSON envelope output (requires \-\-json\-envelope)

.TP
\fB\-\-thumbnail\-size\fR \fI\,WxH\/\fR
Thumbnail dimensions as WxH (default: 160x90 video, 160x160 image)

.TP
\fB\-\-output\fR \fI\,FILE\/\fR
Write output to FILE instead of stdout

.TP
\fB\-\-clear\-ignored\fR
Clear the ignored\-pairs list and exit

.TP
\fB\-\-log\fR \fI\,FILE\/\fR
Append JSON\-lines action log to FILE (one record per deletion/move/link)

.TP
\fB\-\-generate\-undo\fR \fI\,LOG_FILE\/\fR
Generate a shell script to undo actions recorded in a \-\-log file

.SH CONFIGURATION \fI\,'duplicates\-detector scan'\/\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-config\fR
Ignore the config file for this run

.TP
\fB\-\-profile\fR \fI\,NAME\/\fR
Load a named profile (from ~/.config/duplicates\-detector/profiles/)

.SH SESSION MANAGEMENT \fI\,'duplicates\-detector scan'\/\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-resume\fR \fI\,SESSION_ID\/\fR
Resume a previously paused scan session (mutually exclusive with directory
arguments)

.TP
\fB\-\-list\-sessions\fR
List available scan sessions and exit

.TP
\fB\-\-delete\-session\fR \fI\,SESSION_ID\/\fR
Delete a specific saved session and exit

.TP
\fB\-\-clear\-sessions\fR
Clear all saved scan sessions and exit

.TP
\fB\-\-pause\-file\fR \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Path to pause control file for GUI integration

.TP
\fB\-\-cache\-stats\fR
Show cache hit/miss statistics in summary

.SH SCAN CONFIGURATION \fI\,'duplicates\-detector scan'\/\fR
.TP
\fB\-\-save\-config\fR
Write current flags to config file and exit

.TP
\fB\-\-show\-config\fR
Print the resolved config (after merge) and exit

.TP
\fB\-\-save\-profile\fR \fI\,NAME\/\fR
Save current flags as a named profile and exit

.TP
\fB\-\-replay\fR \fI\,FILE\/\fR
Load previously generated JSON envelope output and re\-apply filters/strategies
without re\-scanning

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
show program's version number and exit

.TP
\fB\-\-print\-completion\fR \fI\,SHELL\/\fR
Print shell completion script and exit
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Scan a directory for duplicate videos:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/videos \-v
.EE
.TP
Scan for duplicate images:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/photos \-\-mode image \-v
.EE
.TP
Scan for duplicate audio files:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/music \-\-mode audio \-v
.EE
.TP
Enable perceptual content hashing for higher accuracy:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/videos \-\-content \-v
.EE
.TP
Interactive review with trash action:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/videos \-i \-\-keep newest \-\-action trash
.EE
.TP
Custom scoring weights:
.EX
duplicates\-detector scan /path/to/videos \-\-weights "filename=30,duration=40,resolution=20,filesize=10"
.EE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/duplicates\-detector/config.toml
Configuration file (TOML format). Use \fB\-\-save\-config\fR to write current settings.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/duplicates\-detector/ignore.json
Persistent false\-positive ignore list. Managed via interactive review (\fBs!\fR command).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/duplicates\-detector/sessions/
Paused scan sessions for \fB\-\-resume\fR.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/duplicates\-detector/
Metadata, content hash, and audio fingerprint caches.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime error.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid arguments.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by Ctrl\-C.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ffprobe (1),
.BR ffmpeg (1),
.BR fpcalc (1)
